‚Ä™I don‚Äôt condone what Amber Heard‚Äôs done. It‚Äôs disgusting, and she should be punished. But we have to remember people can change and can redeem themselves.

comment: I have a real problem with your stance on boycotting Aquaman2 if Heard is in it because it's diametrically opposed to your usual stance on this kind of thing.  Yes, people make mistakes.  I don't think it's up to lynch mobs to adjudicate those mistakes, just like when Heard had accused Johnny, or when Chloe Dykstra accused Christ Hardwick and on and on.  Maybe there's some weird evidence that will come out in the case that throws a different light on her actions, even though I'd be hard pressed to imagine what that could be at this point.  However, in a just society, this is up to the courts to decide.  If she's guilty, she'll have to, at the very least, pay a boatload of cash in a settlement, if not serve actual time, and hopefully that will prompt her to seek treatment and rethink her life.  But if you're calling for her to never work again rather than letting the justice system decide her penalty, you're acting no better than a Zoe Quinn and putting yourself above the justice system.  Don't be the guy that heads the lynch mob because he believes he is justified.  It reflects very badly on you.
